      • getOrderOptions

        public List<OrderOption> getOrderOptions()
        oder options Gets the value of the orderOptions property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the orderOptions property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

         getOrderOptions().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list OrderOption

      • getAdditionalData

        public List<AdditionalData> getAdditionalData()
        additional data list Gets the value of the additionalData property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the additionalData property.
